@startuml
title Activity Diagram - Generate And Export Attendance Report

skinparam linetype ortho

|Administrator|
start

:Administrator opens Generate Reports screen;

|JavaFX GUI|
:System displays optional filters;

|Administrator|
:Administrator selects filters;

note right
Filters may include:
semesters, teacher, subject, group,
class type, date from, date to.
Null or empty means unrestricted.
end note

:Administrator clicks Generate Report;

|JavaFX GUI|
:System builds AttendanceReportFilter;

|Services / Repositories|
:ClassMeetingRepository finds matching ClassMeetings;

if (Matching meetings found?) then (yes)
  :System finds involved students through ClassMeeting -> StudentGroup -> Students;
  :AttendanceRepository loads attendance records for matching meetings;
  :System calculates counts per student;
  :Calculate attendancePercentage = (present + late) / totalMeetings * 100;
  :Create AttendanceReport and ReportLine objects;
  :Calculate overallPerformancePercentage;
  :Build conclusion message;
  |Database|
  :Save report with lines;
  |JavaFX GUI|
  :Display report table and conclusion;
else (no)
  |JavaFX GUI|
  :Create empty/no-result report result;
  :Show no data message;
endif

|Administrator|
if (Administrator clicks Export CSV?) then (yes)
  |JavaFX GUI|
  if (Report generated?) then (yes)
    if (Report has lines?) then (yes)
      |Administrator|
      :Administrator chooses target file;
      |Services / Repositories|
      :ReportExportService writes metadata and report lines;
      |File System|
      :Create CSV file;
      |JavaFX GUI|
      :Show export success message;
    else (no)
      |JavaFX GUI|
      :Show "Cannot export an empty report.";
    endif
  else (no)
    |JavaFX GUI|
    :Show "Generate a report before exporting.";
  endif
else (no)
endif

stop
@enduml
